Emergency Response Program Summary

PXP has developed written emergency response procedures to address all elements that may be encountered during planning, responding or following up to an emergency at the Inglewood facility. Application of the emergency response procedures ensures compliance with Cal/OSHA CCR Title 8, Section 5189 Process Safety Management (PSM) of Acutely Hazardous Materials and the emergency response element of the PSM. The basic concept of PXP's emergency procedures are to provide a comprehensive approach for managing emergencies. The four elements of this approach are prevention, preparedness, response, and recovery.

The Emergency Response Action Plan (ERAP) is designed to be applicable to any type of emergency that may affect PXP and based on the concept that the elements of emergency response are similar, regardless of the hazard. It contains pages from the Integrated Contingency Plan (ICP). The ERAP contains the following sections:

1. Facility Information;
2. Notifications;
3. Initial Response Actions;
4. Evacuation Plans/Emergency Shutdown Procedures;
5. Oil Pipeline Route; and
6. Ballona Creek Boom and Staging Locations.


